HEADWORD: Nonelectrical
<hw>Non`e*lec"tric*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not electric;
conducting electricity.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not powered by electricity; -- of machines, tools,
or devices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonelectric</ent>⟦br⟧
